NAME: Autoimmune liver disease panel
DESCRIPTION: An autoimmune liver disease panel is a group of tests that is done to check for autoimmune liver disease.

NAME: Blood Cell Count with Differential
DESCRIPTION: A hematologic procedure to determine the number of red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets, including the white cell differential count and red cell morphology, in a blood sample.

NAME: Blood Cell Count
DESCRIPTION: The determination of the number of red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets in a blood sample.

NAME: Blood Flow Cytometry
DESCRIPTION: Flow cytometry used to examine and quantitate the constituents of the blood.

NAME: Chemistry Test
DESCRIPTION: A laboratory test designed for the quantification of an organic or inorganic chemical within a biological specimen.

NAME: Comprehensive Metabolic Panel
DESCRIPTION: Comprehensive Metabolic Panel

NAME: Drug Test
DESCRIPTION: A laboratory test of biological material such as blood, urine, hair, saliva or sweat, used to detect the presence of a drug or its metabolites with in the body.

NAME: Fasting Lipid Profile
DESCRIPTION: Fasting Lipid Profile

NAME: Hormone measurement
DESCRIPTION: The determination of the amount of hormone present in a sample.

NAME: Immunology Test
DESCRIPTION: Laboratory test involving interaction of antigens with specific antibodies

NAME: Laboratory test related to hemostasis
DESCRIPTION: Laboratory test related to hemostasis

NAME: Mixed-Meal Tolerance Test
DESCRIPTION: Mixed-Meal Tolerance Test

NAME: Protein or Enzyme Type Measurement
DESCRIPTION: A term that refers to a chemistry test measuring a specific protein or enzyme in the peripheral blood or body fluid.

NAME: Renal Function Test
DESCRIPTION: A laboratory procedure that evaluates the kidney function.

NAME: Serum protein electrophoresis
DESCRIPTION: Serum protein electrophoresis

NAME: Thyroid Panel
DESCRIPTION: Thyroid Panel

NAME: Total Protein Measurement
DESCRIPTION: A quantitative measurement of the amount of total protein present in a sample.

NAME: Urinalysis
DESCRIPTION: Laboratory analysis of urine, commonly used to aid in the diagnosis of disease or to detect the presence of a specific substance. It involves examination of the urine by physical or chemical means as well as microscopic examination that helps to screen for urinary tract infections, renal disease, and diseases of other organs, that result in abnormal metabolites (break-down products) appearing in the urine.

NAME: Vitamin measurement
DESCRIPTION: Vitamin level

NAME: serum antibody level
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the amount of an immunoglobulin molecule possessing a specific amino acid sequence that binds to a specific antigen, a substance introduced into an organism which initiates an immune response including the production of the very antibodies which bind to it in an effort to destroy it, in a specified sample of serum, the clear liquid that separates from blood after it has clotted completely, i.e. blood plasma from which fibrinogen has been removed. NAME: Blood Measurement
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the blood, it's contents, cells or other factors contained within the blood.
